                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">391.1164/108: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-21T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 21, 1939—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. Department’s 50, October 11, noon. You may inform the Iranian Government that
                    Dr. William James Hutchins, President Emeritus of Berea College, has been
                    designated by the Mission Board as one of its representatives in the forthcoming
                    discussions. Both he and Dr. Dodds, who were unable to sail on October 14,
                    expect to leave shortly for Tehran.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
